{"folder":"yidKUkah88xNeRf1","name":"Knowledge (Philosophy)","type":"skill","img":"systems/brp/assets/Icons/skills.svg","system":{"description":"<p><strong>Philosophy</strong>: The study of existence and its meaning, from basic logic to&nbsp; existentialism, nihilism, and beyond. Use this skill to remember the precepts of a particular philosophy, identify the philosophical leanings of an author or speaker&rsquo;s argument, and to engage in philosophical debate.</p>\n<hr>\n<p>This skill represents experience or academic study of a branch of knowledge. Use a Knowledge skill to remember pertinent facts, to analyze or identify clues, make logical suppositions, and recall impressive trivia. For more scientific ones, see Science skill. A fumble results in misleading and inaccurate falsehoods, and successes yield more useful and detailed information.</p>\n<p><strong>Specialties</strong>: Accounting, Anthropology, Archaeology, History, Law, Occult, Religion, etc. The gamemaster should determine whether the Knowledge skill has a base chance of 05% for specialties that are common, or 00% for those requiring research and study to even have a rudimentary understanding of.</p>\n<p><strong>Setting Notes</strong>: In fantasy and historical settings, only a small subset of specialties exist. As settings grow more modern, specialties increase.</p>\n<p><strong>System Notes</strong>: The optional EDU characteristic and Knowledge roll cover most&nbsp; common knowledge&mdash;specialized information is represented by an appropriate specialty of a Knowledge skill.</p>","gmDescription":"","subType":"","base":5,"xp":0,"profession":0,"personality":0,"personal":0,"effects":0,"baseFormula":{"1":{"stat":"fixed","value":0},"2":{"stat":"fixed","value":0},"Func":"or"},"noXP":false,"category":"mntlmod","chosen":true,"specialism":true,"group":false,"groupSkills":[],"prsnlty":false,"variable":false,"specName":"Philosophy","mainName":"Knowledge","occupation":false,"improve":false},"effects":[],"flags"