{"folder":"JCyftuSyyx7RVaSW","name":"Drive (Truck)","type":"skill","img":"systems/brp/assets/Icons/skills.svg","system":{"description":"<p>Use Drive to steer, maneuver, and control a ground vehicle, whether pulled by animals or powered by an engine. For common vehicles, the base chance is 20%, for unknown/uncommon vehicles, it&rsquo;s 01%. A fumble when driving normally means the vehicle may not start, or a collision or crash. Success means your character gets where they&rsquo;re going, or is able to correct a bad condition (like a slide or spin), and superior successes mean more distance covered in less time, less fuel used, or some other benefit.&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Specialties</strong>: Automobile, Bicycle, Carriage, Cart, Chariot, Dogsled, Motorcycle, Truck, Sleigh, etc.&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Setting Notes</strong>: Adjust the base chance by the user&rsquo;s familiarity where appropriate, but when in doubt, assume that base principles apply.</p>\n<p><strong>System Notes</strong>: Most day-to-day driving is an Automatic task&mdash;a Drive roll is only required under adverse conditions or for extraordinary driving (speeding through a busy downtown area, chasing another vehicle, etc.). To tail another vehicle without being noticed, use an opposed Drive roll vs. the other driver&rsquo;s Spot. To resolve vehicle chases, use the Chases rules.</p>","gmDescription":"","subType":"","base":20,"xp":0,"profession":0,"personality":0,"personal":0,"effects":0,"baseFormula":{"1":{"stat":"fixed","value":0},"2":{"stat":"fixed","value":0},"Func":"or"},"noXP":false,"category":"physmod","chosen":true,"specialism":true,"group":false,"groupSkills":[],"prsnlty":false,"variable":false,"specName":"Truck","mainName":"Drive","occupation":false,"improve":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"brp","systemVersion":"11.0.37","coreVersion":"11.315","createdTime":1699094618571,"modifiedTime":1702582643340,"lastModifiedBy":"NiJh555W408VQRFB"},"_id":"6hDVvi4yA5AhQGai","sort":0,"ow