{"folder":"TObATz4QmCl9DsS4","name":"Pilot (Submarine)","type":"skill","img":"systems/brp/assets/Icons/skills.svg","system":{"description":"<p>Use this skill to steer, maneuver, and control a vehicle through the air, on or under the water, or in space. Larger vehicles may require multiple pilots, and a roll should be made every four hours when not in combat, and once per round during combat or when performing vehicular maneuvers.</p>\n<p><strong>Specialties:</strong> Airplane, Airship, Balloon, Boat, Helicopter, Hovercraft, Jet Aircraft, Jetpack, Starship, Submarine, etc. At the gamemaster&rsquo;s discretion, a pilot may pilot a vessel with a similar specialty as if Difficult. If successful, make an&nbsp; experience check. If the experience roll is successful, start a new skill with a specialty at that rating, plus the gained experience.</p>\n<p><strong>Effects</strong>: Most day-to-day piloting is Automatic&mdash;roll only under adverse conditions or for extraordinary situations. A fumble almost inevitably causes an engine to stall or even crash, failing means the destination is not reached in the desired timeframe, success gets where one desires, and superior successes yield more expert piloting and results. See Aerial Combat and Chases rules for more information, and the Chase Trouble table&nbsp;for mishaps.</p>","gmDescription":"","subType":"","base":1,"xp":0,"profession":0,"personality":0,"personal":0,"effects":0,"baseFormula":{"1":{"stat":"fixed","value":0},"2":{"stat":"fixed","value":0},"Func":"or"},"noXP":false,"category":"physmod","chosen":true,"specialism":true,"group":false,"groupSkills":[],"prsnlty":false,"variable":false,"specName":"Submarine","mainName":"Pilot","occupation":false,"improve":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{}},"_stats":{"systemId":"brp","systemVersion":"11.0.37","coreVersion":"11.315","createdTime":1699092618107,"modifiedTime":1702582643340,"lastModifiedBy":"NiJh555W408VQRFB"},"_id":"Z6xj2qqSP4DQpm8J","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"NiJh555W408VQRFB":3}}
{"folder":"yidKUkah88xNeRf1","name":"Knowledge (Academic Lore)","type":"skill","img":"systems/brp/assets/Icons/skills.svg","system":{"description":"<p><strong>Academic Lore (Ancient Eras Only): </strong>In eras when the whole of written knowledge can be contained in a single library, this represents how &lsquo;learned&rsquo; one is. Use it like a Knowledge roll for nearly any area of knowledge.</p>\n<hr>\n<p>This skill represents experience or academic study of a branch of knowledge. Use a Knowledge skill to remember pertinent facts, to analyze or identify clues, make logical suppositions, and recall impressive trivia. For more scientific ones, see Science skill. A fumble results in misleading and inaccurate falsehoods, and successes yield more useful and detailed information.</p>\n<p><strong>Specialties</strong>: Accounting, Anthropology, Archaeology, History, Law, Occult, Religion, etc. The gamemaster should determine whether the Knowledge skill has a base chance of 05% for specialties that are common, or 00% for those requiring research and study to even have a rudimentary understanding of.</p>\n<p><strong>Setting Notes</strong>: In fantasy and historical settings, only a small subset of specialties exist. As settings grow more modern, specialties increase.</p>\n<p><strong>System Notes</strong>: The optional EDU characteristic and Knowledge roll cover most&nbsp; common knowledge&mdash;specialized information is represented by an appropriate specialty of a Knowledge skill.&nbsp;</p>","gmDescription":"","subType":"","base":5,"xp":0,"profession":0,"personality":0,"personal":0,"effects":0,"baseFormula":{"1":{"stat":"fixed","value":0},"2":{"stat":"fixed","value":0},"Func":"or"},"noXP":false,"category":"mntlmod","chosen":true,"specialism":true,"group":false,"groupSkills":[],"prsnlty":false,"variable":false,"specName":"Academic Lore","mainName":"Knowledge","occupation":false,"improve":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{}},"_stats":{"systemId":"brp","systemVersion":"11.0.37","coreVersion":"11.315","createdTime":1699091788533,"modifiedTime":1702582643340,"lastModifiedBy":"NiJh555W408VQRFB"},"_id":"ZHx6wosR2A82UPhz","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"NiJh555W408VQRFB":3}}
{"folder":"TObATz4QmCl9DsS4","name":"Pilot (Boat)","type":"skill","img":"systems/brp/assets/Icons/skills.svg","system":{"description":"<p>Use this skill to steer, maneuver, and control a vehicle through the air, on or under the water, or in space. Larger vehicles may require multiple pilots, and a roll should be made every four hours when not in combat, and once per round during combat or when performing vehicular maneuvers.</p>\n<p><strong>Specialties:</strong>&nbsp;Airplane, Airship, Balloon, Boat, Helicopter, Hovercraft, Jet Aircraft, Jetpack, Starship, Submarine, etc. At the gamemaster&rsquo;s discretion, a pilot may pilot a vessel with a similar specialty as if Difficult. If successful, make an&nbsp; experience check. If the experience roll is successful, start a new skill with a specialty at that rating, plus the gained experience.</p>\n<p><strong>Effects</strong>: Most day-to-day piloting is Automatic&mdash;roll only under adverse conditions or for extraordinary situations. A fumble almost inevitably causes an engine to stall or even crash, failing means the destination is not reached in the desired timeframe, success gets where one desires, and superior successes yield more expert piloting and results. See Aerial Combat and Chases rules for more information, and the Chase Trouble table for mishaps.</p>","gmDescription":"","subType":"","base":1,"xp":0,"profession":0,"personality":0,"personal":0,"effects":0,"baseFormula":{"1":{"stat":"fixed","value":0},"2":{"stat":"fixed","value":0},"Func":"or"},"noXP":false,"category":"physmod","chosen":true,"specialism":true,"group":false,"groupSkills":[],"prsnlty":false,"variable":false,"specName":"Boat","mainName":"Pilot","occupation":false,"improve":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"brp","systemVersion":"11.0.37","coreVersion":"11.315","createdTime":1699092618107,"modifiedTime":1702582643340,"lastModifiedBy":"NiJh555W408VQRFB"},"_id":"ZYpMLWgiUYtIu42q","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"NiJh555W408VQRFB":3}}
{"folder":"ZIlDG4BZ4J53B8xV","name":"Language (own)","type":"skill","img":"systems/brp/assets/Icons/skills.svg","system":{"description":"<p>The ability to communicate verbally in a language, either one&rsquo;s native language or another. Other languages can be learned in the home, at school, on the streets, or at school, depending on the culture and upbringing. Most characters begin&nbsp; knowing their own language at INT&times;5. Bilingual characters must have spent skill points on another language skill. Day-to-day conversation in one&rsquo;s own Language is Automatic and does not require a skill roll. Skill rolls are only required when communicating difficult concepts or in difficult and unusual situations, such as translating. This skill covers verbal communication&mdash;reading and writing use Literacy. A fumble means disastrous misunderstanding, while successes yield smooth and sometimes eloquent communication.&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Specialties</strong>: Per language. Each specialty applies to a single language; if you wish for your character to learn an additional language, they must build up an&nbsp; additional Language skill.</p>\n<p><strong>System Notes</strong>: If the EDU optional rule is used, choose the higher of INT&times;5 or EDU&times;5 for the base chance. Understanding obscure dialects or ancient varieties of a language is Difficult. Complex or long documents or conversations with several salient points might require multiple language rolls to understand, one for each point. See the Language Fluency table below for details about how skill rating impacts communication and fluency.</p>\n<table style=\"width: 100%; height: 175.333px;\" border=\"1\"><colgroup><col style=\"width: 16.4862%;\"><col style=\"width: 83.5687%;\"></colgroup>\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 17.3333px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 17.3333px;\"><strong>Skill Rating</strong></td>\n<td style=\"height: 17.3333px;\"><strong>Fluency</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 52px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 52px;\">01-05</td>\n<td style=\"height: 52px;\">Knows only a few dozen words, can count to 10. May only communicate simple ideas. Complex communication (Bargain, Persuade, etc.) is out of the question. For&nbsp; example, &ldquo;Food. Please sell me.&rdquo;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 54px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 54px;\">06-25</td>\n<td style=\"height: 54px;\">Gets across simple requests, enough to be understood and survive day to day. Complex communication (Bargain, Persuade, etc.) are Difficult. For example, &ldquo;How much moneys for this leg of lamb?&rdquo;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17.3333px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 17.3333px;\">26-50</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17.3333px;\">Assured communication. The speaker can speak better than a child, getting most ideas across. Communication skills are not restricted, but certain actions may still be Difficult. For example, &ldquo;How much? But this lamb was much cheaper yesterday!&rdquo;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17.3333px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 17.3333px;\">51-75</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17.3333px;\">Allows speaker to tell stories, sagas, songs, etc. Idioms and jokes become accessible. Can pass for native. Complex communications are now rolled at the speaker&rsquo;s full skill ranking. For example, &ldquo;Look at this cut! The lamb was rotten before it was butchered and is clearly not even worth the sweat of the laborer who carried it here.&rdquo;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17.3333px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 17.3333px;\">76-00</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17.3333px;\">The language of poets, philosophers, scientists, and diplomats. Not only can the speaker pass for native, but they can also mimic one or more local dialects. Jargon and obscure forms of speech come easily. For example, &ldquo;Surely the assessment of this specimen of provender could be reevaluated in light of its advanced state of decomposition.&rdquo;</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>","gmDescription":"","subType":"","base":0,"xp":0,"profession":0,"personality":0,"personal":0,"effects":0,"baseFormula":{"1":{"stat":"int","value":5},"2":{"stat":"edu","value":5},"Func":"or"},"noXP":false,"category":"cmmnmod","chosen":true,"specialism":true,"group":false,"groupSkills":[],"prsnlty":false,"variable":true,"specName":"own","mainName":"Language","occupation":false,"improve":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"brp","systemVersion":"11.0.37","coreVersion":"11.315","createdTime":1699091850420,"modifiedTime":1702582643340,"lastModifiedBy":"NiJh555W408VQRFB"},"_id":"a5BsE6Jq0GJC91XS","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"NiJh555W408VQRFB":3}}
{"folder":"tEQd66hWQK7v4DPe","name":"Throw Knife","type":"skill","img":"systems/brp/assets/Icons/skills.svg","system":{"description":"<p>Use this to wield any hand-held self-propelled missile weapon such as bows, crossbows, throwing axes, spears, throwing stars, javelins, blowguns, spear guns, or even boomerangs. For grenades, use Throw.</p>\n<p><strong>Specialties</strong>: Specialties are equivalent to weapon classes. Each specialty applies to weapons from that category of weapon only: but the gamemaster may allow use of a similar weapon class as if Difficult. If successful, make an experience check. If the experience roll is successful, start a new skill with a specialty at that rating, plus the gained experience.</p>\n<p><strong>System Notes</strong>: All missile weapons have a minimum STR and DEX required to use the weapon. Typically,&nbsp; the attacker&rsquo;s damage modifier is halved for missile&nbsp; weapons, and for entirely self-propelled weapons (blowguns, crossbows, etc.), the damage modifier is not applied. Missile Weapon can be used for aimed attacks.</p>","gmDescription":"","subType":"missile","base":15,"xp":0,"profession":0,"personality":0,"personal":0,"effects":0,"baseFormula":{"1":{"stat":"fixed","value":0},"2":{"stat":"fixed","value":0},"Func":"or"},"noXP":false,"category":"zcmbtmod","chosen":false,"specialism":false,"group":false,"groupSkills":[],"prsnlty":false,"variable":false,"specName":"","mainName":"Throw Knife","occupation":false,"improve":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"brp","systemVersion":"11.0.37","coreVersion":"11.315","createdTime":1699422028452,"modifiedTime":1702582643340,"lastModifiedBy":"NiJh555W408VQRFB"},"_id":"aCybS6TJQ0dSLbXx","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"NiJh555W408VQRFB":3}}
{"folder":"ZIlDG4BZ4J53B8xV","name":"Art (specify)","type":"skill","img":"systems/brp/assets/Icons/skills.svg","system":{"description":"<p>Use this skill to create a work of art in paint or sculpture, or to compose a story, poem, or musical work. A critical or special success yields a timeless classic of considerably more value and prestige, a failure is mediocre hackwork, and a fumble may harm the creator&rsquo;s reputation.</p>\n<p>You would use Perform for acting, dancing, singing, or&nbsp;playing a musical&nbsp; instrument.</p>\n<p><strong>Specialties</strong>: Calligraphy, Composing, Conceptual Art, Digital Art, Drawing, Painting, Photography, Poetry, Sculpture, Sketching, Songwriting, Writing, etc.</p>\n<p><strong>Setting Notes</strong>: Art is universal, though it may have era- or settingspecific specialties.</p>","gmDescription":"","subType":"","base":5,"xp":0,"profession":0,"personality":0,"personal":0,"effects":0,"baseFormula":{"1":{"stat":"fixed","value":0},"2":{"stat":"fixed","value":0},"Func":"or"},"noXP":false,"category":"mnplmod","chosen":false,"specialism":true,"group":false,"groupSkills":[],"prsnlty":false,"variable":false,"specName":"specify","mainName":"Art","occupation":false,"improve":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"brp","systemVersion":"11.0.37","coreVersion":"11.315","createdTime":1699084864720,"modifiedTime":1702582643340,"lastModifiedBy":"NiJh555W408VQRFB"},"_id":"acOstCP79clQmqTm","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"NiJh555W408VQRFB":3}}
{"folder":"mgRE8c77fALWsnRC","name":"Science (Psychology)","type":"skill","img":"systems/brp/assets/Icons/skills.svg","system":{"description":"<p>Use this skill to know scientific information and principles from a particular field, and to observe phenomena and draw data-based conclusions. Related information includes the history of the science, familiarity with the equipment and methodology, and an awareness of significant figures and schools of thought in that specialty.&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Specialties</strong>: Astronomy, Behavioral Science, Biology, Botany, Chemistry (or Alchemy), Cryptography, Genetics, Geology, Mathematics, Meteorology, Natural History, Pharmacology, Physics, Planetology, Psychology, Quantum Mechanics, Xenobiology, Zoology, etc. At the gamemaster&rsquo;s discretion, skill with a related specialty may be rolled as if Difficult, though a successful roll does not yield an experience check or the chance to begin a new skill with that specialty.</p>\n<p><strong>System Notes</strong>: Many Science specialties require specialized equipment, measuring instruments, computers, or even a laboratory. Science rolls can take anywhere&nbsp; from 30 minutes to weeks or months, at the gamemaster&rsquo;s discretion: four hours for an experiment is a good average. Attempting a Science roll without sufficient time or equipment is either Difficult or Impossible</p>","gmDescription":"","subType":"","base":1,"xp":0,"profession":0,"personality":0,"personal":0,"effects":0,"baseFormula":{"1":{"stat":"fixed","value":0},"2":{"stat":"fixed","value":0},"Func":"or"},"noXP":false,"category":"mntlmod","chosen":true,"specialism":true,"group":false,"groupSkills":[],"prsnlty":false,"variable":false,"specName":"Psychology","mainName":"Science","occupation":false,"improve":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{}},"_stats":{"systemId":"brp","systemVersion":"11.0.37","coreVersion":"11.315","createdTime":1699092828405,"modifiedTime":1702582643340,"lastModifiedBy":"NiJh555W408VQRFB"},"_id":"bwwUnrOCrfgWBVxo","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"NiJh555W408VQRFB":3}}
