{"folder":"4d8QNRrsmDRBZltY","name":"Heavy Machine (Turbines)","type":"skill","img":"systems/brp/assets/Icons/skills.svg","system":{"description":"<p>Use this skill to operate any machine larger than a person and any wheeled vehicle heavier than a moving van, such as a forklift, tank, bulldozer, crane, locomotive, or operate the engines on a large seagoing vessel. Heavy Machine also covers basic care and preventative maintenance, though once a heavy machine fails, a Repair skill is required to fix it. For aircraft, use the Pilot skill. A fumble results in a crash, engine troubles, and/or property damage, while failure means the machine doesn&rsquo;t do the desired task. Successes and superior successes indicate greater&nbsp; effectiveness.</p>\n<p><strong>Specialties:</strong> By vehicle type (Armored Vehicles, Boilers, Bulldozers, Cranes,&nbsp; Engines, Turbines, etc.).</p>\n<p><strong>System Notes</strong>: Generally, heavy machines are unable to participate in chases, but certain kinds of machines can be used as weapons, doing 3D6 to 6D6 damage, based on the size of the device. Using this skill outside normal performance is Difficult, as is operation and maintenance in extreme conditions.&nbsp;</p>","gmDescription":"","subType":"","base":1,"xp":0,"profession":0,"personality":0,"personal":0,"effects":0,"baseFormula":{"1":{"stat":"fixed","value":0},"2":{"stat":"fixed","value":0},"Func":"or"},"noXP":false,"category":"mnplmod","chosen":true,"specialism":true,"group":false,"groupSkills":[],"prsnlty":false,"variable":false,"specName":"Turbines","mainName":"Heavy Machine","occupation":false,"improve":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{}},"_stats":{"systemId":"brp","systemVersion":"11.0.37","coreVersion":"11.315","createdTime":1699091028774,"modifiedTime":1702582643340,"lastModifiedBy":"NiJh555W408VQRFB"},"_id":"cPVDFmHfqHNWo3d2","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"NiJh555W408VQRFB":3}}
{"folder":"5KHpLcKfsoKihnbx","name":"Repair (Electronics)","type":"skill","img":"systems/brp/assets/Icons/skills.svg","system":{"description":"<p>Equipment and other objects get damaged or stop working. Use Repair to fix them or make slight modifications and adaptations.</p>\n<p><strong>Specialties</strong>: Electrical, Electronic, Engineering, Hydroelectric, Mechanical,&nbsp; Structural, Quantum, etc.</p>\n<p><strong>Effects</strong>: A fumble damages the item further and could even hurt the one making the repair attempt (1D3 hit points for either, for example) and makes further repairs&nbsp; Difficult. Failure accomplishes nothing, success restores 1D3 hit points and the item becomes usable again or returns to working order. Superior successes yield similar benefits, perhaps using the First Aid skill and the gamemaster&rsquo;s judgement as a guide. A critical may even improve the item in some small way, such as adding to its total hit point, armor points, or adding a slight bonus when it is utilized.</p>","gmDescription":"","subType":"","base":15,"xp":0,"profession":0,"personality":0,"personal":0,"effects":0,"baseFormula":{"1":{"stat":"fixed","value":0},"2":{"stat":"fixed","value":0},"Func":"or"},"noXP":false,"category":"mnplmod","chosen":true,"specialism":true,"group":false,"groupSkills":[],"prsnlty":false,"variable":false,"specName":"Electronics","mainName":"Repair","occupation":false,"improve":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"brp","systemVersion":"11.0.37","coreVersion":"11.315","createdTime":1699092741211,"modifiedTime":1702582643340,"lastModifiedBy":"NiJh555W408VQRFB"},"_id":"cSbMnKPkh115Fr6A","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"NiJh555W408VQRFB":3}}
{"folder":"yidKUkah88xNeRf1","name":"Knowledge (Group)","type":"skill","img":"systems/brp/assets/Icons/skills.svg","system":{"description":"<p><strong>Group/Subspecialty</strong>: General information about a particular culture, nationality, group, club, or social class. Use this skill to identify a member of that group, know &lsquo;who&rsquo;s who&rsquo; within that group, and remember social customs and mores of the&nbsp; group.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<hr>\n<p>This skill represents experience or academic study of a branch of knowledge. Use a Knowledge skill to remember pertinent facts, to analyze or identify clues, make logical suppositions, and recall impressive trivia. For more scientific ones, see Science skill. A fumble results in misleading and inaccurate falsehoods, and successes yield more useful and detailed information.</p>\n<p><strong>Specialties</strong>: Accounting, Anthropology, Archaeology, History, Law, Occult, Religion, etc. The gamemaster should determine whether the Knowledge skill has a base chance of 05% for specialties that are common, or 00% for those requiring research and study to even have a rudimentary understanding of.</p>\n<p><strong>Setting Notes</strong>: In fantasy and historical settings, only a small subset of specialties exist. As settings grow more modern, specialties increase.</p>\n<p><strong>System Notes</strong>: The optional EDU characteristic and Knowledge roll cover most&nbsp; common knowledge&mdash;specialized information is represented by an appropriate specialty of a Knowledge skill.</p>","gmDescription":"","subType":"","base":5,"xp":0,"profession":0,"personality":0,"personal":0,"effects":0,"baseFormula":{"1":{"stat":"fixed","value":0},"2":{"stat":"fixed","value":0},"Func":"or"},"noXP":false,"category":"mntlmod","chosen":true,"specialism":true,"group":false,"groupSkills":[],"prsnlty":false,"variable":false,"specName":"Group","mainName":"Knowledge","occupation":false,"improve":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":