{"folder":"yloOQanUI1XemuSF","name":"Pistol, Revolver or Rifle","type":"skill","_id":"clWGWY2RfzJjMtEN","img":"systems/brp/assets/Icons/skills.svg","system":{"description":"","gmDescription":"","subType":"","base":0,"xp":0,"profession":0,"personality":0,"personal":0,"effects":0,"baseFormula":{"1":{"stat":"fixed","value":0},"2":{"stat":"fixed","value":0},"Func":"or"},"noXP":false,"category":"cmmnmod","chosen":false,"specialism":false,"group":true,"groupSkills":["KBtVq36d1GuYHAxz","zlIZEQKDTPQ0odFU","tjWYH5drKa3AZX2z"],"prsnlty":false,"variable":false,"specName":"","mainName":"Pistol, Revolver or Rifle","occupation":false,"improve":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"brp","systemVersion":"11.0.37","coreVersion":"11.315","createdTime":1701015088720,"modifiedTime":1702582643340,"lastModifiedBy":"NiJh555W408VQRFB"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"NiJh555W408VQRFB":3}}
{"folder":"ZIlDG4BZ4J53B8xV","name":"Sleight of Hand","type":"skill","_id":"cqG7R4JpJe4ynxpX","img":"systems/brp/assets/Icons/skills.svg","system":{"description":"<p>Use his skill to manipulate small objects (dice, cards, coins, wallets, letters, etc.) in a misleading manner or without attracting attention, such as when picking pockets, cheating at cards, or performing stage magic. A skills&nbsp;fumble is glaringly obvious: whether the item is dropped, or the wouldbe thief is caught with their hand in the target&rsquo;s pocket. Failure means nothing is accomplished, and a unsuspecting target succeeding in an Idea roll may realize that they are being duped.</p>\n<p><strong>System Notes</strong>: The skill is opposed by Spot where appropriate. Once an object has been palmed or taken, use Hide to hide it from a concerted search.</p>","gmDescription":"","subType":"","base":5,"xp":0,"profession":0,"personality":0,"personal":0,"effects":0,"baseFormula":{"1":{"stat":"fixed","value":0},"2":{"stat":"fixed","value":0},"Func":"or"},"noXP":false,"category":"mnplmod","chosen":false,"specialism":false,"group":false,"groupSkills":[],"prsnlty":false,"variable":false,"specName":"","mainName":"Sleight of Hand","occupation":false,"improve":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"brp","systemVersion":"11.0.37","coreVersion":"11.315","createdTime":1699092984203,"modifiedTime":1702582643340,"lastModifiedBy":"NiJh555W408VQRFB"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"NiJh555W408VQRFB":3}}
{"folder":"yidKUkah88xNeRf1","name":"Knowledge (Anthropology)","type":"skill","img":"systems/brp/assets/Icons/skills.svg","system":{"description":"<p><strong>Anthropology</strong>: The study of cultures, including customs, art, and behavior. Use it to identify a person or artifact&rsquo;s native culture or to determine a culture&rsquo;s social mores and behaviors.</p>\n<hr>\n<p>This skill represents experience or academic study of a branch of knowledge. Use a Knowledge skill to remember pertinent facts, to analyze or identify clues, make logical suppositions, and recall impressive trivia. For more scientific ones, see Science skill. A fumble results in misleading and inaccurate falsehoods, and successes yield more useful and detailed information.</p>\n<p><strong>Specialties</strong>: Accounting, Anthropology, Archaeology, History, Law, Occult, Religion, etc. The gamemaster should determine whether the Knowledge skill has a base chance of 05% for specialties that are common, or 00% for those requiring research and study to even have a rudimentary understanding of.</p>\n<p><strong>Setting Notes</strong>: In fantasy and historical settings, only a small subset of specialties exist. As settings grow more modern, specialties increase.</p>\n<p><strong>System Notes</strong>: The optional EDU characteristic and Knowledge roll cover most&nbsp; common knowledge&mdash;specialized information is represented by an appropriate specialty of a Knowledge skill.</p>","gmDescription":"","subType":"","base":5,"xp":0,"profession":0,"personality":0,"personal":0,"effects":0,"baseFormula":{"1":{"stat":"fixed","value":0},"2":{"stat":"fixed","value":0},"Func":"or"},"noXP":false,"category":"mntlmod","chosen":true,"specialism":true,"group":false,"groupSkills":[],"prsnlty":false,"variable":false,"specName":"Anthropology","mainName":"Knowledge","occupation":false,"improve":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"brp","systemVersion":"11.0.37","coreVersion":"11.315","createdTime":1699091788533,"modifiedTime":1702582643340,"lastModifiedBy":"NiJh555W408VQRFB"},"_id":"d7Ob04diBKGyeUll","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"NiJh555W408VQRFB":3}}
{"folder":"yidKUkah88xNeRf1","name":"Knowledge (Blasphemous Lore)","type":"skill","img":"systems/brp/assets/Icons/skills.svg","system":{"description":"<p><strong>Blasphemous Lore</strong>: The study of horrific occult secrets and ancient evils. The more of this knowledge your character has, the less their grasp on sanity. See the&nbsp; optional Sanity rules for more information. Blasphemous Lore skill begins at 0%,&nbsp; not 05%, and cannot be increased with experience.</p>\n<hr>\n<p>This skill represents experience or academic study of a branch of knowledge. Use a Knowledge skill to remember pertinent facts, to analyze or identify clues, make logical suppositions, and recall impressive trivia. For more scientific ones, see Science skill. A fumble results in misleading and inaccurate falsehoods, and successes yield more useful and detailed information.</p>\n<p><strong>Specialties</strong>: Accounting, Anthropology, Archaeology, History, Law, Occult, Religion, etc. The gamemaster should determine whether the Knowledge skill has a base chance of 05% for specialties that are common, or 00% for those requiring research and study to even have a rudimentary understanding of.</p>\n<p><strong>Setting Notes</strong>: In fantasy and historical settings, only a small subset of specialties exist. As settings grow more modern, specialties increase.</p>\n<p><strong>System Notes</strong>: The optional EDU characteristic and Knowledge roll cover most&nbsp; common knowledge&mdash;specialized information is represented by an appropriate specialty of a Knowledge skill.</p>","gmDescription":"","subType":"","base":0,"xp":0,"profession":0,"personality":0,"personal":0,"effects":0,"baseFormula":{"1":{"stat":"fixed","value":0},"2":{"stat":"fixed","value":0},"Func":"or"},"noXP":true,"category":"mntlmod","chosen":true,"specialism":true,"group":false,"groupSkills":[],"prsnlty":false,"variable":false,"specName":"Blasphemous Lore","mainName":"Knowledge","occupation":false,"improve":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{}},"_stats":{"systemId":"brp","systemVersion":"11.0.37","coreVersion":"11.315","createdTime":1699091788533,"modifiedTime":1702582643340,"lastModifiedBy":"NiJh555W408VQRFB"},"_id":"eokwKmFPHvidSX1X","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"NiJh555W408VQRFB":3}}
{"folder":"ZIlDG4BZ4J53B8xV","name":"Projection","type":"skill","_id":"ew1oTsAUTuhNzoQK","img":"systems/brp/assets/Icons/skills.svg","system":{"description":"<p>This optional skill is used by superheroes to &lsquo;fire&rsquo; or direct a superpower at a target. It can be increased in character generation if the character has superpowers and is subject to the power level limitations.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Use this skill to direct powered attacks at a target using powers such as Energy Projection, Snare Projection, and others. Choose how your character emits this power&mdash; hands, eyes, or from a device. When the power is used, on a fumble the power points are lost, consult the Missile Weapon Fumbles table for additional guidance (interpreted as necessary). Failure goes wide of the target: roll 1D4 to see if the projection falls in front, behind, to the right, or to the left of the target. Make a Luck roll to avoid collateral damage such as striking an innocent bystander, an ally, or causing structural damage. Success strikes the target, and a special success hits it with additional precision and may do additional damage or have an increased effect. A critical, as always, is perfectly executed to maximum effect. If a combat power, use the guidance for special and critical successes.</p>\n<p><strong>System Notes</strong>: Your character&rsquo;s damage modifier is never included in any projected superpower. Line of sight is required for Projection. Modifiers that apply to missile or ranged attacks also apply. Projection may be used for aimed attacks. Projection can be dodged, like a missile weapon, though the Dodge roll may be Difficult.</p>","gmDescription":"","subType":"","base":0,"xp":0,"profession":0,"personality":0,"personal":0,"effects":0,"baseFormula":{"1":{"stat":"dex","value":2},"2":{"stat":"fixed","value":0},"Func":"or"},"noXP":false,"category":"physmod","chosen":false,"specialism":false,"group":false,"groupSkills":[],"prsnlty":false,"variable":true,"specName":"","mainName":"Projection","occupation":false,"improve":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"brp","systemVersion":"11.0.37","coreVersion":"11.315","createdTime":1699092648219,"modifiedTime":1702582643340,"lastModifiedBy":"NiJh555W408VQRFB"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"NiJh555W408VQRFB":3}}
{"folder":"ZIlDG4BZ4J53B8xV","name":"Command","type":"skill","img":"systems/brp/assets/Icons/skills.svg","system":{"description":"<p>Use this skill to inspire, direct, and coordinate subordinates, guiding them in complex tasks and improving the effectiveness of the group. Military officers, noblemen, politicians, and business executives are made or broken based on their ability to manage and lead.</p>\n<p>Personality, a strong voice, and an iron will are invaluable tools of command. A fumble incites insurrection, failing is uninspiring and confusing, and success allows you to add 1/5 your Command skill as a complementary skill bonus to all your subordinates for each round you command them, so long as they follow your orders. Roll every round in combat, or every turn in mass combat.</p>\n<p><strong>System Notes</strong>: Used primarily in combat, though it can extend to corporate negotiations, etc. Artillery, Heavy Weapon, Melee Weapon, Missile Weapon, and Strategy are the most appropriate skills to receive this benefit.</p>","gmDescription":"","subType":"","base":5,"xp":0,"profession":0,"personality":0,"personal":0,"effects":0,"baseFormula":{"1":{"stat":"fixed","value":0},"2":{"stat":"fixed","value":0},"Func":"or"},"noXP":false,"category":"cmmnmod","chosen":false,"specialism":false,"group":false,"groupSkills":[],"prsnlty":false,"variable":false,"specName":"","mainName":"Command","occupation":false,"improve":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"brp","systemVersion":"11.0.37","coreVersion":"11.315","createdTime":1699084782472,"modifiedTime":1702582643340,"lastModifiedBy":"NiJh555W408VQRFB"},"_id":"f0sw4MmVyqrawjs3","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"NiJh555W408VQRFB":3}}
{"folder":"Rm7UTqLlatCQ30WB","name":"Perform (Ritual)","type":"skill","img":"systems/brp/assets/Icons/skills.svg","system":{"description":"<p>Use this skill to perform, whether acting, dancing, playing an instrument, singing, or exhibiting some other forms of artistic expression. A fumble is a humiliation, failure is uninspiring, while successes yield positive attention, cheers, and perhaps critical acclaim and financial rewards. If recorded and distributed, it may continue to inspire and earn far after the original performance.</p>\n<p><strong>Specialties</strong>: Act, Conduct Orchestra, Dance, Juggle, Orate, Play Instrument (subspeciality), Recite, Ritual, Sing, etc.&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>System Notes</strong>: Successful use of the Perform (Ritual) skill may augment a magic power or cause it to have additional benefits, at the gamemaster&rsquo;s discretion.</p>","gmDescription":"","subType":"","base":5,"xp":0,"profession":0,"personality":0,"personal":0,"effects":0,"baseFormula":{"1":{"stat":"fixed","value":0},"2":{"stat":"fixed","value":0},"Func":"or"},"noXP":false,"category":"cmmnmod","chosen":true,"specialism":true,"group":false,"groupSkills":[],"prsnlty":false,"variable":false,"specName":"Ritual","mainName":"Perform","occupation":false,"improve":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"brp","systemVersion":"11.0.37","coreVersion":"11.315","createdTime":1699092566542,"modifiedTime":1702582643340,"lastModifiedBy":"NiJh555W408VQRFB"},"_id":"fOm4CIiXD5sEoWIv","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"NiJh555W408VQRFB":3}}
{"folder":"pa1iFJDN5vnbh7cz","name":"Art (Composing)","type":"skill","img":"systems/brp/assets/Icons/skills.svg","system":{"description":"<p>Use this skill to create a work of art in paint or sculpture, or to compose a story, poem, or musical work. A critical or special success yields a timeless classic of considerably more value and prestige, a failure is mediocre hackwork, and a fumble may harm the creator&rsquo;s reputation.</p>\n<p>You would use Perform for acting, dancing, singing, or&nbsp;playing a musical&nbsp; instrument.</p>\n<p><strong>Specialties</strong>: Calligraphy, Composing, Conceptual Art, Digital Art, Drawing, Painting, Photography, Poetry, Sculpture, Sketching, Songwriting, Writing, etc.</p>\n<p><strong>Setting Notes</strong>: Art is universal, though it may have era- or settingspecific specialties.</p>","gmDescription":"","subType":"","base":5,"xp":0,"profession":0,"personality":0,"personal":0,"effects":0,"baseFormula":{"1":{"stat":"fixed","value":0},"2":{"stat":"fixed","value":0},"Func":"or"},"noXP":false,"category":"mnplmod","chosen":true,"specialism":true,"group":false,"groupSkills":[],"prsnlty":false,"variable":false,"specName":"Composing","mainName":"Art","occupation":false,"improve":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"brp","systemVersion":"11.0.37","coreVersion":"11.315","createdTime":1699084864720,"modifiedTime":1702582643340,"lastModifiedBy":"NiJh555W408VQRFB"},"_id":"fQPpiTMOn11YZ8ul","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"NiJh555W408VQRFB":3}}
{"folder":"4d8QNRrsmDRBZltY","name":"Heavy Machine (Boilers)","type":"skill","img":"systems/brp/assets/Icons/skills.svg","system":{"description":"<p>Use this skill to operate any machine larger than a person and any wheeled vehicle heavier than a moving van, such as a forklift, tank, bulldozer, crane, locomotive, or operate the engines on a large seagoing vessel. Heavy Machine also covers basic care and preventative maintenance, though once a heavy machine fails, a Repair skill is required to fix it. For aircraft, use the Pilot skill. A fumble results in a crash, engine troubles, and/or property damage, while failure means the machine doesn&rsquo;t do the desired task. Successes and superior successes indicate greater&nbsp; effectiveness.</p>\n<p><strong>Specialties:</strong> By vehicle type (Armored Vehicles, Boilers, Bulldozers, Cranes,&nbsp; Engines, Turbines, etc.).</p>\n<p><strong>System Notes</strong>: Generally, heavy machines are unable to participate in chases, but certain kinds of machines can be used as weapons, doing 3D6 to 6D6 damage, based on the size of the device. Using this skill outside normal performance is Difficult, as is operation and maintenance in extreme conditions.&nbsp;</p>","gmDescription":"","subType":"","base":1,"xp":0,"profession":0,"personality":0,"personal":0,"effects":0,"baseFormula":{"1":{"stat":"fixed","value":0},"2":{"stat":"fixed","value":0},"Func":"or"},"noXP":false,"category":"mnplmod","chosen":true,"specialism":true,"group":false,"groupSkills":[],"prsnlty":false,"variable":false,"specName":"Boilers","mainName":"Heavy Machine","occupation":false,"improve":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{}},"_stats":{"systemId":"brp","systemVersion":"11.0.37","coreVersion":"11.315","createdTime":1699091028774,"modifiedTime":1702582643340,"lastModifiedBy":"NiJh555W408VQRFB"},"_id":"faDXMzLFn7ilj6ft","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"NiJh555W408VQRFB":3}}
{"folder":"TObATz4QmCl9DsS4","name":"Pilot (Helicopter)","type":"skill","img":"systems/brp/assets/Icons/skills.svg","system":{"description":"<p>Use this skill to steer, maneuver, and control a vehicle through the air, on or under the water, or in space. Larger vehicles may require multiple pilots, and a roll should be made every four hours when not in combat, and once per round during combat or when performing vehicular maneuvers.</p>\n<p><strong>Specialties:</strong>&nbsp;Airplane, Airship, Balloon, Boat, Helicopter, Hovercraft, Jet Aircraft, Jetpack, Starship, Submarine, etc. At the gamemaster&rsquo;s discretion, a pilot may pilot a vessel with a similar specialty as if Difficult. If successful, make an&nbsp; experience check. If the experience roll is successful, start a new skill with a specialty at that rating, plus the gained experience.</p>\n<p><strong>Effects</strong>: Most day-to-day piloting is Automatic&mdash;roll only under adverse conditions or for extraordinary situations. A fumble almost inevitably causes an engine to stall or even crash, failing means the destination is not reached in the desired timeframe, success gets where one desires, and superior successes yield more expert piloting and results. See Aerial Combat and Chases rules for more information, and the Chase Trouble table for mishaps.</p>","gmDescription":"","subType":"","base":1,"xp":0,"profession":0,"personality":0,"personal":0,"effects":0,"baseFormula":{"1":{"stat":"fixed","value":0},"2":{"stat":"fixed","value":0},"Func":"or"},"noXP":false,"category":"physmod","chosen":true,"specialism":true,"group":false,"groupSkills":[],"prsnlty":false,"variable":false,"specName":"Helicopter","mainName":"Pilot","occupation":false,"improve":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{}},"_stats":{"systemId":"brp","systemVersion":"11.0.37","coreVersion":"11.315","createdTime":1699092618107,"modifiedTime":1702582643340,"lastModifiedBy":"NiJh555W408VQRFB"},"_id":"fis2vBwRWkdkvriA","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"NiJh555W408VQRFB":3}}
{"folder":"ZIlDG4BZ4J53B8xV","name":"Fly (non-winged creature)","type":"skill","img":"systems/brp/assets/Icons/skills.svg","system":{"description":"<p>For beings with wings, the appropriate gear (antigravity belt, rocket boots, etc.), or flight powers, use this skill to maneuver in the air without a vehicle. Use Fly to&nbsp; perform aerial maneuvers or acrobatics without losing control, outmaneuver a foe in aerial combat, or fly in poor weather conditions.</p>\n<p>Base chance is DEX&times;4 for&nbsp; winged creatures; 1/2 DEX for all others.&nbsp; For jet packs, hang-gliders, etc. use the Pilot skill</p>\n<p><strong>Effects</strong>: Fly has specific effects:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Fumble: Stall and perhaps even fall. Winged characters must make a successful Stamina roll or suffer 1D3&ndash;1 points of damage from a sprain or strain. A device stalls or fails and cannot keep your character aloft. The flyer falls one round per altitude level above the ground. Make a Difficult Fly roll to stay aloft&mdash;failing means a crash.</li>\n<li>Failure: Off course or drops to an undesirable altitude. Goes nowhere.</li>\n<li>Success: Completes the desired maneuver or holds position in a chase</li>\n<li>Special: Completes the desired maneuver and gains a +10% bonus to the next Dodge, Fly or attack roll made in aerial combat.</li>\n<li>Critical: Completes the desired maneuver and gains a bonus of +25% to the next Dodge, Fly or attack roll made in aerial combat.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>System Notes</strong>: Short, uneventful flights under normal or moderate conditions are Automatic. See Weather Conditions for modifiers to flight. Stamina rolls are&nbsp; required for long-range flights, with the characteristic multiplier decreasing by one every four hours or fraction thereof spent in the air. Normal flight does not&nbsp; expend fatigue points, while maneuvering or stressful flight is a strenuous activity. Flying while wearing armor or heavy gear incurs a penalty equal to your&nbsp; character&rsquo;s current ENC total. A flying character carrying a heavy object must match their STR against the SIZ of the&nbsp; carried object on the resistance table to stay aloft.</p>","gmDescription":"","subType":"","base":0,"xp":0,"profession":0,"personality":0,"personal":0,"effects":0,"baseFormula":{"1":{"stat":"dex","value":0.5},"2":{"stat":"fixed","value":0},"Func":"or"},"noXP":false,"category":"physmod","chosen":false,"specialism":false,"group":false,"groupSkills":[],"prsnlty":false,"variable":true,"specName":"","mainName":"Fly (non-winged creature)","occupation":false,"improve":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"brp","systemVersion":"11.0.37","coreVersion":"11.315","createdTime":1699091262901,"modifiedTime":1702582643340,"lastModifiedBy":"NiJh555W408VQRFB"},"_id":"fovsaOBInLCS5QMl","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"NiJh555W408VQRFB":3}}
