{"folder":"yidKUkah88xNeRf1","name":"Knowledge (Streetwise)","type":"skill","img":"systems/brp/assets/Icons/skills.svg","system":{"description":"<p><strong>Streetwise</strong>: Knowledge of the shadier segments of a society, from the protocols of the poor to the ways of the criminal underworld. Use this skill to find a safehouse, identify a fence for stolen goods, or know who to ask for other semi-legal or illegal favors.</p>\n<hr>\n<p>This skill represents experience or academic study of a branch of knowledge. Use a Knowledge skill to remember pertinent facts, to analyze or identify clues, make logical suppositions, and recall impressive trivia. For more scientific ones, see Science skill. A fumble results in misleading and inaccurate falsehoods, and successes yield more useful and detailed information.</p>\n<p><strong>Specialties</strong>: Accounting, Anthropology, Archaeology, History, Law, Occult, Religion, etc. The gamemaster should determine whether the Knowledge skill has a base chance of 05% for specialties that are common, or 00% for those requiring research and study to even have a rudimentary understanding of.</p>\n<p><strong>Setting Notes</strong>: In fantasy and historical settings, only a small subset of specialties exist. As settings grow more modern, specialties increase.</p>\n<p><strong>System Notes</strong>: The optional EDU characteristic and Knowledge roll cover most&nbsp; common knowledge&mdash;specialized information is represented by an appropriate specialty of a Knowledge skill.</p>","gmDescription":"","subType":"","base":5,"xp":0,"profession":0,"personality":0,"personal":0,"effects":0,"baseFormula":{"1":{"stat":"fixed","value":0},"2":{"stat":"fixed","value":0},"Func":"or"},"noXP":false,"category":"mntlmod","chosen":true,"specialism":true,"group":false,"groupSkills":[],"prsnlty":false,"variable":false,"specName":"Streetwise","mainName":"Knowledge","occupation":false,"improve":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{}},"_stats":{"systemId":"brp","systemVersion":"11.0.37","coreVersion":"11.315","createdTime":1699091788533,"modifiedTime":1702582643340,"lastModifiedBy":"NiJh555W408VQRFB"},"_id":"szCdftJk5sjtFPqT","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"NiJh555W408VQRFB":3}}
{"folder":"SVz6XHbLVZZ1hGmR","name":"Other Melee Weapon","type":"skill","img":"systems/brp/assets/Icons/skills.svg","system":{"description":"<p>Use this skill to wield a particular type of weapon in hand-to-hand combat, whether attacking or parrying.</p>\n<p><strong>Specialties</strong>: Specialties are equivalent to weapon classes.&nbsp;Each specialty applies to weapons from that category of weapon only: but the gamemaster may allow use of a similar weapon class as if Difficult. If successful, make an experience check. If the experience roll is successful, start a new skill with a specialty at that rating, plus the gained experience.</p>\n<p><strong>System Notes</strong>: Your character can attempt more than one parry per round, but each roll after the first is made at a cumulative &ndash;30%. At the gamemaster&rsquo;s discretion, your character can wield a weapon from a related or similar weapon category, with the roll being Difficult.</p>","gmDescription":"","subType":"melee","base":5,"xp":0,"profession":0,"personality":0,"personal":0,"effects":0,"baseFormula":{"1":{"stat":"fixed","value":0},"2":{"stat":"fixed","value":0},"Func":"or"},"noXP":false,"category":"zcmbtmod","chosen":false,"specialism":false,"group":false,"groupSkills":[],"prsnlty":false,"variable":false,"specName":"","mainName":"Other Melee Weapon","occupation":false,"improve":false},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"brp","systemVersion":"11.0.37","coreVersion":"11.315","createdTime":1699092192092,"modifiedTime":1702582643340,"lastModifiedBy":"NiJh555W408VQRFB"},"_id":"tDVr8jmLNYe3a3bD","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"NiJh555W408VQRFB":3}}
{"folder":"yidKUkah88xNeRf1","name":"Knowledge (Politics)","type":"skill","img":"systems/brp/assets/Icons/skills.svg","system":{"description":"<p><strong>Politics</strong>: The study and knowledge of political systems or other means of governance imposed upon or elected by the citizenry. Use this skill to understand the major power blocs in an area, how to influence the political structure, and how citizens will react to political change or influence.</p>\n<hr>\n<p>This skill represents experience or academic study of a branch of knowledge. Use a Knowledge skill to remember pertinent facts, to analyze or identify clues, make logical suppositions, and recall impressive trivia. For more scientific ones, see Science skill. A fumble results in misleading and inaccurate falsehoods, and successes yield more useful and detailed information.</p>\n<p><strong>Specialties</strong>: Accounting, Anthropology, Archaeology, History, Law, Occult, Religion, etc. The gamemaster should determine whether the Knowledge skill has a base chance of 05% for specialties that are common, or 00% for those requiring research and study to even have a rudimentary understanding of.</p>\n<p><strong>Setting Notes</strong>: In fantasy and historical settings, only a small subset of specialties exist. As settings grow more modern, specialties increase.</p>\n<p><strong>System Notes</strong>: The optional EDU characteristic and Knowledge roll cover most&nbsp; common knowledge&mdash;specialized information is represented by an appropriate specialty of a Knowledge skill.</p>","gmDescription":"","subType":"","base":5,"xp":0,"profession":0,"personality":0,"personal":0,"effects":0,"baseFormula":{"1":{"stat":"fixed","value":0},"2":{"stat":"fixed","value":0},"Func":"or"},"noXP":false,"category":"mntlmod","chosen":true,"specialism":true,"group":false,"groupSkills":[],"prsnlty":false,"variable":false,"specName":"Politics","mainName":"Knowledge","occupation":false,"improve":false},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{}}